node.text: Continuing through our 10 year anniversary journey, I wanted to talk about what I think the purpose of classroom decor is. You definitely don’t need it to be an amazing teacher! The joy of teaching will always be in your heart!  However, decor can help bring joy when you feel good in your environment whether it’s one bulletin board you are proud of OR the way your entire room flows. It can help you stay organized and enhance teaching in a fun and purposeful way. Listen in as I share my thoughts on this topic. 🥰 #classroomdecor #schoolgirlstyle

node.title: How classroom decor can bring joy❣️

node.text:
My last post about meeting the SGS team. 🙌🏻🙌🏻
I adore @malekindergartenteacher and I am excited to share his story below! 
🤍🤍🤍
Hi, I'm Chad! 
I have been working as a Design Assistant with Melanie since 2019. You may have also seen me in the background of every classroom makeover, making sure that every border is level and has a perfectly scalloped corner. Fun fact, some people call me the border king, but I’ll leave that up for debate.
When I’m not working for Melanie, I’m decorating my own classroom and working with students! This will be my 9th year of teaching. I taught kindergarten for 8 years, and I am now a reading consultant with a focus on our most at-risk students. Teaching is my first passion, but design is very close behind.
So how did I meet Melanie? I met Melanie 6 years ago working for an educational company. We knew we were best friends when we both couldn’t find our hotel rooms after coming back from dinner one evening. Don’t worry, we finally found our rooms, but we still laugh about it to this day! To say that we are two peas in a pod would be an understatement.
What I love about Melanie is that she is the most kind-hearted, selfless, and caring person. She continually puts others first, and she is one of the most creative and hardworking individuals that I have met. Melanie's passion for teaching, curriculum, and classroom decor is infectious. She inspires me to be a better person each day and to always follow my dreams.
I am beyond blessed to be part of the Schoolgirl Style team, and I am so excited for what the future has in store! @malekindergartenteacher @schoolgirlstyle 
#schoolgirlstyle #meettheteam #10yearsofsgs

node.text: Schoolgirl Style has taken me on quite the journey, and there are a few moments during the last ten years that really stand out to me. Today I wanted to share one of the memories that I treasure! #classroommakeover #10yearsofsgs #10yearanniversary #grateful #lifeisbeautiful #behindthescenes

node.text:
I thought it might be fun to go through a few of my classrooms over the years! I always enjoyed the process of getting them ready each summer. 🙌🏻🙌🏻🙌🏻
Pictured here:
1. Woodland Whimsy
2. Sweet Blue Bird
3. Twinkle, Twinkle, You’re a Star
4. Confetti Crush
5. Color my Classroom
6. Happy Camper 
Ahhh! I have such fond memories of these spaces.
